<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb92ad5e4-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s1661"><num value="1661">§ 1661.</num><heading> Robbery ashore</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Whoever, being engaged in any piratical cruise or enterprise, or being of the crew of any piratical vessel, lands from such vessel and commits robbery on shore, is a pirate, and shall be imprisoned for life.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb92ad5e5-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645">June 25, 1948, ch. 645</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/775">62 Stat. 775</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
